<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1876-05-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1876-05-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="129" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d129">
                        <head>No. 119.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hoffman</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1876-05-01"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 1,
                                1876</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">Fish</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary, Washington:</hi></p>
                        <p>Informed by foreign office Winslow will be discharged on third, unless
                            arrangement made. Reply to note promised in few days. Have asked he may
                            be detained till answer received and communicated to you. Meantime
                            matter will come up in Parliament.</p>
                        <p>Copy eight sixty-four sent Lord Derby Saturday, with note.</p>
                        <closer><signed>HOFFMAN.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>